  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] We-- we-- we-- we crossed-- we crossed the the Bug River to the city that was called Brest-Litovsk.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The Poles called it [POLISH].",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "This city is very famous-- was famous for a peace treaty that the Germans dictated to the Russians in the first World War.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And there is a citadel there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It's called the Brest Citadel.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And the peace treaty-- that treaty, I think, it was in 1917-- it was called the Brest [POLISH] Treaty.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The reason why they sent us over there was that the train that supplied the lines, the German armies, passed through a forest that was 20 or 30 kilometers long through the forest, and the soil in that area is very swampy and sandy-- very, very soft.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the partisans, Russian partisans, that were operating in these forests had a ball of being hidden in the forest and to lay mines under those lines and to blast the German trains that were shipping in-- were going in-- with material.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was very easy because the soil was soft and you could one, two, three, dig out under the ties to put a mine under there and blow up the trains.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The Germans were suffering heavily from the partisans blowing up these trains, and they decided that the only way to get rid of that is to cut completely 1/2 a kilometer on each side of the-- of the rails.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Cut it down so that nobody that can hide so close that they would see.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
